msIdentifier.repository: Quaker and Special Collections, Rendel Harris

msContents.summary: Eastern Syriac rite including liturgical prayers for various feasts and Sundays; begins abruptly; many prayers attributed to Eliyá III, Catholicos of the Church of the East (died 1190); also includes a prayer for the lack of rain (f. 100v-101v). Many pages repaired along top and gutter.

author.name: J. Rendel Harris Collection (Quaker & Special Collections, Haverford College)

supportDesc.extent: iv stubs, xvi, 125, ii leaves : 200 x 145 (153 x 91) mm bound to 208 x 150 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Partial pagination [1-139] in Hindu-Arabic numerals in ink, bottom, center; Modern foliation in pencil added, upper left recto. References in the record are to the modern foliation.

decoDesc.decoNote: Textblock ruled in double red; rubrications in red; text division decorative markers in red and black (for example, f. 6v, 97v-98r).

binding.p: Modern cardboard with mottled grey and green sides; red spine.

origin.p: Copy completed on 7 April 1677 (AG 1988) at the Rabban Hormizd Monastery, in Alqūsh, Iraq by ʼEliyā (f. 101v-102r, 113r-114v).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by J. Rendel Harris.

keywords.term: Church of the East--Prayers and devotions
